atory material makes accessible the historical context of the subject and highlights the insights offered by the documents as well as the pitfalls to be avoided in this area of historical enquiry.This volume aims to provide a coherent working collection of texts for lecturers, teachers and students who wish to understand the experience of Jewish Europeans in this period.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aChristianity and other religionsxSources. 0aJewsxHistoryy70-1789xSources. 0aJewszEuropexHistoryxSources. 0aJudaismxRelationsxChristianityxHistoryxSources. 4aMedieval Sources 2013. 7aHISTORY / Jewish.2bisacsh  aChristian authorities.  aEuropean Jews.  aJewish devilishness.  aJewish economic activities.  aJews' financial relations.  aReformation.  aeconomic culture.  amedieval Church.  asocial problems.  asocial relations.1 aEdwards, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEdwards, John, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152611269940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526112699423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526112699/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles